io.github.struppigel.parser.sections.rsrc

Class ResourceDirectoryEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.struppigel.parser.sections.rsrc.ResourceDirectoryEntry
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataEntry, SubDirEntry

    public abstract class ResourceDirectoryEntry
extends java.lang.Object
    The entry of a ResourceDirectory

    There are two types of resource directory entries. They either point to another resource directory table or to data.

    The entries have either an ID or a Name

        public static ResourceDirectoryEntry apply(java.io.File file,
                                           boolean isNameEntry,
                                           byte[] entryBytes,
                                           int entryNr,
                                           Level level,
                                           long virtualAddress,
                                           long rsrcOffset,
                                           MemoryMappedPE mmBytes,
                                           ResourceLoopChecker loopChecker)
        Creates a ResourceDirectoryEntry

        Parameters:
        file - the PE file
        isNameEntry - indicates whether the ID is a number id or points to a name
        entryBytes - the array of bytes this entry is made of
        entryNr - the number of the entry within the ResourceDirectory
        level - the level of the ResourceDirectory this entry is a member of
        virtualAddress - the rva to the resource table
        rsrcOffset - the relative offset from the resource table to the resource directory entry
        mmBytes - the memory mapped PE
        loopChecker - the resource loop checker
        Returns:
        ResourceDirectoryEntry
